            <p:rationale>The organizational structure is subject to change.  The fact that an activity is now performed by one person does not mean that the same is true in a different organizational structure.  Also, with organizational change comes undesirable change: systems may be open to hacking where they were not before. </p:rationale>
            <p:implications>Role definitions are as much as possible based on the process and not the structure of the organization. Activities that, at another probable time, might be performed by another person with a distinct potential must be defined (OTOPOP) as separate from each other.</p:implications>
